race.comment: WOODSTOCK ROCK (1) grows a leg for rider Wiggins who is yet to miss a drum in eight steers and will be high on confidence following a dominant win here last time out. Sure to be right there at the business end again. OUTWITTED (4) was a touch disappointing at the latest effort but the form prior was full of merit. Worth another chance. TIZSO FAB (3) has won two of his past three. Was below par two back at Bundaberg then bounced back with a win over 1400m at this track last time out. Sure to measure up and must be included in calculations. OUTTA CONTROL (8) resumed over 1200m at this track last start and finished fifth. Fitter and a top-three hope.
